---
import logoG from "../../assets/logo_g.PNG";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Manifesto - Glyph" description="Why I built Glyph: a local-first markdown notes app for macOS." bodyClass="has-dot-grid">
	<div class="manifesto-page">
		<header class="manifesto-header">
			<a href="/" class="manifesto-logo">
				<img src={logoG.src} alt="" class="manifesto-logo-icon" />
				<span>GLYPH</span>
			</a>
			<a href="/" class="manifesto-home">Back home</a>
		</header>

		<main class="manifesto-main">
			<p class="manifesto-label">MANIFESTO</p>
			<h1>Why I built Glyph</h1>

			<div class="manifesto-body">
				<section class="manifesto-section">
					<p class="section-numeral">I</p>
					<p>Where do your notes actually live?</p>
					<p>
						Most note apps ship them to a server you don't own. Some rank
						your words for engagement. Others lock your writing behind a
						subscription you have to keep paying to read what you wrote
						last year.
					</p>
					<p>
						You wanted a blank page. The industry sold you a workflow.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="manifesto-section">
					<p class="section-numeral">II</p>
					<p>Notes belong on your machine.</p>
					<p>
						In files you can open with any text editor. A markdown file
						from 2010 still opens today. A note inside a defunct cloud
						app does not.
					</p>
					<p>
						So Glyph keeps every note as a plain .md file in a folder
						you choose, on a disk you own.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="manifesto-section">
					<p class="section-numeral">III</p>
					<p>A notebook should be quiet.</p>
					<p>
						It shouldn't ping you, push an upgrade, or feed your drafts
						into someone's training set. It should open fast and hold
						your words.
					</p>
					<p>
						You decide when AI helps. You pick the model. You can turn
						it off and lose nothing.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="manifesto-section">
					<p class="section-numeral">IV</p>
					<p>Less is harder.</p>
					<p>
						Every feature you don't use still costs you a toggle, a
						panel, or a permission you have to dismiss. I'd rather ship
						a small app that fits your workflow than a big one you have
						to manage.
					</p>
					<p>
						So Glyph stays small on purpose.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="manifesto-section">
					<p class="section-numeral">V</p>
					<p>You own the files.</p>
					<p>
						Glyph keeps everything in markdown on your disk and indexes
						it with a local SQLite database. Nothing leaves your machine
						unless you ask. If I shut Glyph down tomorrow, every note
						still opens in any editor.
					</p>
					<p>
						That's the point of the whole project.
					</p>
				</section>

				<div class="manifesto-coda">
					<p>Open Glyph.</p>
					<p>Your words stay yours.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</main>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.manifesto-page {
		width: min(680px, 90vw);
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 2.5rem 0 5rem;
	}

	.manifesto-header {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}

	.manifesto-logo {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.45rem;
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 0.14em;
	}

	.manifesto-logo-icon {
		width: 1.25rem;
		height: 1.25rem;
		border-radius: 4px;
	}

	.manifesto-home {
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--muted);
		border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
		transition: color 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease;
	}

	.manifesto-home:hover {
		color: var(--ink);
		border-color: rgba(17, 17, 17, 0.2);
	}

	.manifesto-label {
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		font-weight: 500;
		letter-spacing: 0.18em;
		color: var(--faint);
		margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
	}

	h1 {
		font-family: var(--serif);
		font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem);
		font-style: italic;
		font-weight: 400;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		line-height: 1.12;
		margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
	}

	.manifesto-body {
		display: grid;
		gap: 2.5rem;
	}

	.manifesto-section {
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.9rem;
	}

	.section-numeral {
		font-family: var(--serif);
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		font-style: italic;
		color: var(--faint);
		margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
	}

	.manifesto-section p:not(.section-numeral) {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		line-height: 1.85;
		color: var(--muted);
	}

	.manifesto-section p:not(.section-numeral):first-of-type + p,
	.manifesto-section p:nth-of-type(2) {
		color: var(--muted);
	}

	.manifesto-section > p:nth-child(2) {
		font-family: var(--sans);
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		font-weight: 500;
		color: var(--ink);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.manifesto-coda {
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
		padding-top: 2rem;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.35rem;
	}

	.manifesto-coda p {
		font-family: var(--serif);
		font-size: 1.3rem;
		font-style: italic;
		color: var(--ink);
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.manifesto-page {
			padding-top: 1.75rem;
		}

		.manifesto-header {
			flex-direction: column;
			align-items: flex-start;
			margin-bottom: 2.25rem;
		}
	}
</style>
